    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Last October, the State Department of Environmental Protection declared an amnesty for companies that had failed to apply for air pollution permits for their smokestacks. For five months, the agency said, businesses could seek the permits without penalty. The agency has reviewed half the 1,151 applications received from 250 companies and has found that in nearly one out of three cases, new pollution control equipment was needed, said Robert C. Shinn Jr., Commissioner of the department.</p>
      </block>
